name: SpinalFusion
title: Spinal Fusion
description:
This set of values identifies patients who have had spinal fusion at the thoracolumbar level or lower which may be a contraindication to neuraxial anesthesia.
NOTE:  VALUE SET UNDER DEVELOPMENT AS MEASURE TESTING IS ONGOING.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values identifies patients who have had spinal fusion at the thoracolumbar level or lower which may be a contraindication to neuraxial anesthesia.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have had a spinal fusion procedure at the thoracolumbar level or lower.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Procedure category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only use codes which represent the surgical procedure of a spinal fusion at the thoracolumbar level or lower.),(Exclusion Criteria: Spinal fusion performed at the occipital-cervical, cervical, cervicothoracic or thoracic vertebral joint levels.)
